## [[download24.png]]Download
Source is freely available. You can browse the [[git repository||http://nitlanguage.org/nit.git]] or download the latest [[snapshot|http://nitlanguage.org/nit.git/snapshot/HEAD.tar.gz]] (tar.gz).

## [[doc24.png]]Documentation
The [[Nit language reference|http://nitlanguage.org/doc/nitreference.pdf]](PDF) is about language syntax, classes and modules.
[[Développez en Nit|http://nitlanguage.org/doc/developpez.pdf]](PDF, in French) is a programmer manual.
The [[standard library|http://nitlanguage.org/doc/stdlib]] references built-ins and standard classes.
You can also look at some [[examples of programs|examples]] written in Nit.

For more details about Nit theoretical foundations, see [[publications and technical reports|research]].
